Octaspire Dern version 0.33.0

usage: ../../build/octaspire-dern-repl [option] ... [file] ...

where [option] is one of the values listed below and every
[file] is loaded and evaluated before the REPL is started or closed.
If any of -e string or [file] is used, REPL is not started unless -i is used.

-n        --no-region-allocator : use regular malloc/free instead of region allocator
-c        --color-diagnostics   : use colors on unix like systems
-i        --interactive         : start REPL after any -e string or [file]s are evaluated
-e string --evaluate string     : evaluate a string without entering the REPL (unless -i is given)
-v        --version             : print version information and exit
-h        --help                : print this help message and exit
